Q1. What is the time complexity of the following code in terms of n?

for (int i = 1; i <= n; i = i * 2)
    for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
        printf("*");,"O(n log n)","O(n)","O(n^2)","O(log n)"

Q2 (Time). Consider:

void recursion(int N) {
    if (N == 0) return;
    printf("%d\n", N);
    recursion(N - 1);
}

What is the TIME complexity?,"O(N)","O(1)","O(2^N)","O(log N)"

Q2 (Space). Consider:

void recursion(int N) {
    if (N == 0) return;
    printf("%d\n", N);
    recursion(N - 1);
}

What is the SPACE complexity?,"O(N)","O(1)","O(log N)","O(2^N)"

Q3. What is the time complexity of the following code?

void calc(int arr[], int N) {
    int j = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
        while (j < N && arr[i] < arr[j]) {
            j++;
        }
    }
},"O(N)","O(log N)","O(N * log N)","O(N^2)"

Q6. Consider the following function intended to free every node of a singly linked list:

void destroyList(struct Node *head) {
    while (head != NULL) {
        free(head);
        head = head->next;
    }
}

What is wrong with this code?,"After free(head), accessing head->next reads freed memory — undefined behavior","The base case is incorrect

Q11. You want to sort the following array of strings alphabetically:

char *names[] = {"banana", "apple", "cherry"};
qsort(names, 3, sizeof(char *), cmp);

Which definition of cmp works correctly?,"int cmp(const void *a, const void *b) {

Q12. Assume a hypothetical system where sizeof(char) = 1, sizeof(int) = 4, alignment is 4 bytes (every member starts at a 4-byte boundary, struct size rounded up to a multiple of 4).

struct S {
    char a;
    int  b;
    char c;
};

What is sizeof(struct S)?,"12","6","9","16"

Q13. On a BIG-ENDIAN system (the most-significant byte is stored at the lowest memory address). Assume sizeof(int) = 4 and sizeof(char) = 1.

union U {
    int  i;
    char c[4];
};
union U u;
u.i = 0x12345678;

What is the value of u.c[0]?,"0x12","0x78","0x34","0x56"

Q15. Consider:

int a[3][4];
int *q       = a[0];
int (*p)[4]  = a;

Initially q and p hold the same address — the address of a[0][0]. After executing q++ and p++ (assume sizeof(int) = 2), by how many bytes have q and p moved, respectively?,"2 bytes, 8 bytes","4 bytes, 16 bytes","8 bytes, 8 bytes","2 bytes, 2 bytes"
